modules.description: Handles path parsing and matching for typed routing. Provides functions to construct route parts from strings, extract path prefixes, and perform wildcard matching. Works directly with string paths and a structured representation of route segments. Useful for defining and matching URL routes in web applications without relying on a specific framework.

This module provides combinators for defining and parsing URL paths with typed parameters, supporting operations like sequence composition, handler binding, and custom type serialization, along with utilities to format and merge route patterns. It works with string-based paths and structured route segments, enabling type-safe navigation and bidirectional routing for applications requiring precise URL schema enforcement or debuggable route introspection. Use cases include building RESTful APIs with validated path parameters, generating URIs from route definitions, and inspecting routing tables during development.
